<PartIntro Id="SDL-RESERVED-hometopic">
<Title>Text Editor Help</Title>
<TitleAbbrev>Text Editor Help</TitleAbbrev>
<Para>Text Editor enables you to create and edit short documents
such as memos, mail messages, or resource files.<IndexTerm>
<Primary>Text Editor: starting</Primary>
</IndexTerm><IndexTerm>
<Primary>starting: Text Editor</Primary>
</IndexTerm><IndexTerm>
<Primary>opening: Text Editor</Primary>
</IndexTerm><IndexTerm>
<Primary>Front Panel control, Text Editor</Primary>
</IndexTerm><IndexTerm>
<Primary>Text Editor: Front Panel control</Primary>
</IndexTerm>
</Para>
<Graphic Entityref="TextEditorWindow" Id="HTXTE.HTOP.fig.1"></Graphic>
<Procedure>
<Title>To open Text Editor:</Title>
<Step>
<Para><Anchor Id="ToOpenTextEditor">
</Para>
<ItemizedList Mark="&bull;">
<ListItem Id="HTXTE.HTOP.item.1">
<Para>Click the Text Editor control in the Front Panel.
</Para>
</ListItem>
</ItemizedList>
<Graphic Entityref="TextEditorButton" Id="HTXTE.HTOP.fig.2"></Graphic>
<Para>You can also start Text Editor using one of these methods:</Para>
<ItemizedList Mark="&bull;">
<ListItem Id="HTXTE.HTOP.item.2">
<Para>Open the Personal Applications subpanel in the Front Panel and click
the Text Editor control.</Para>
<Graphic Entityref="TextEditorSubpanel" Id="HTXTE.HTOP.fig.3"></Graphic>
</ListItem>
<ListItem Id="HTXTE.HTOP.item.3">
<Para>Drag a file icon to the Text Editor control in the Front Panel.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem Id="HTXTE.HTOP.item.4">
<Para>Double-click a data file icon in File Manager.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem Id="HTXTE.HTOP.item.5">
<Para>Select a data file icon in File Manager and choose Open from the
Selected menu.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem Id="HTXTE.HTOP.item.6">
<Para>Type the following command in a Terminal window:
</Para>
</ListItem>
</ItemizedList>
<ProgramListing>dtpad <Symbol Role="Variable">filename</Symbol> &amp; 
</ProgramListing>
</Step>
</Procedure>
